{
  "texts": [
    "A duality argument in combination with Ornstein's result is carried out by McMullen [33] who uses this idea to show lack of Lipschitz solutions for the divergence equation:div u = f,for some right sides f ∈ L ∞.",
    "This result was, however, first obtained by Preiss [39] using a different technique.",
    "Bouragin and Brezis [10] provide a number of results for the divergence equation in various limiting cases and in particular provide a simpler duality argument, akin to McMullen's approach, showing the lack of Lipschitz solutions.",
    "It appears that a similar method could be used for any under determined linear differential operator, but this is not available explicitly in literature.Our Theorem 1.4 may thus be seen as a multilinear (as opposed to linear) version of these types of statements.",
    "It is clear that linearised Lipschitz non-regularity is a statement about lack of regularity near L ∞."
  ]
}